1
00:00:14,300 --> 00:00:17,833
<i>Friend, if I may suggest,
you should get the surgery.</i>

2
00:00:19,067 --> 00:00:20,867
<i> Right away.</i>

3
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:24,600
<i>Didn't I promise to
take care of you?</i>

4
00:00:24,733 --> 00:00:26,733
<i> Thank you, friend.</i>

5
00:00:26,867 --> 00:00:29,067
<i>Don't make me look
like an idiot.</i>

6
00:00:29,200 --> 00:00:30,967
<i>What are you planning
to do to Felma?</i>

7
00:00:31,100 --> 00:00:32,733
<i> I'm not making you look dumb.</i>

8
00:00:32,867 --> 00:00:34,367
<i> You're just really dumb.</i>

9
00:00:34,533 --> 00:00:35,700
<i> You were together in Davao,</i>

10
00:00:35,833 --> 00:00:37,700
<i>and nothing happened
between you?</i>

11
00:00:37,833 --> 00:00:38,900
<i> No, Hazel.</i>

12
00:00:39,033 --> 00:00:42,067
<i>Even if you keep trying,
I won't team up with you.</i>

13
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:44,533
<i>I won't force
Felma to love me.</i>

14
00:00:44,667 --> 00:00:49,167
<i>Because I know no one can
replace Manuel in her heart.</i>

15
00:00:49,300 --> 00:00:52,200
<i>You know, bro, when I heard
what you said to Hazel,</i>

16
00:00:52,333 --> 00:00:54,333
<i> my anger disappeared.</i>

17
00:00:54,467 --> 00:00:56,433
<i> So did my jealousy.</i>

18
00:00:56,567 --> 00:00:58,533
<i>And I admired you
for who you are.</i>

19
00:00:58,667 --> 00:01:00,433
<i> I'm managing, Manuel.</i>

20
00:01:00,567 --> 00:01:02,767
<i>Because I respect you and Felma.</i>

21
00:01:02,900 --> 00:01:05,967
<i>And I hope we can be friends,
bro.</i>

22
00:01:06,100 --> 00:01:08,467
<i> Real friends.</i>

23
00:01:08,633 --> 00:01:09,033
<i> Bro?</i>

24
00:01:09,167 --> 00:01:10,100
<i> Bro.</i>

25
00:01:10,233 --> 00:01:13,933
<i>I need to tell you
something about Hazel.</i>

26
00:01:14,067 --> 00:01:15,800
<i> She's not your friend.</i>

27
00:01:15,933 --> 00:01:18,100
<i>Felma, she's not a good person.</i>

28
00:01:18,233 --> 00:01:19,100
<i> What?</i>

29
00:01:19,233 --> 00:01:20,767
<i> I'm scared, Doctor.</i>

30
00:01:20,900 --> 00:01:23,133
<i> I might not come out alive.</i>

31
00:01:23,267 --> 00:01:26,733
<i>But I'm also scared that
if I don't have the surgery...</i>

32
00:01:26,867 --> 00:01:30,667
<i>I might completely forget
the people I love.</i>

33
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:32,433
<i>I'll go through
with the surgery.</i>

34
00:01:36,733 --> 00:01:37,867
Okay.

35
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:41,433
So, where would you like the
surgery to be done, Miss Felma?

36
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:43,367
Is it here in Southcrest

37
00:01:43,500 --> 00:01:47,300
or in Davao
with Dr. Emil Yunque?

38
00:01:49,933 --> 00:01:53,867
Emil said Felma shouldn't
travel anymore.

39
00:01:57,133 --> 00:01:59,167
And he highly recommends
this hospital.

40
00:02:02,667 --> 00:02:05,700
They have one of the best
neurosurgical teams

41
00:02:05,833 --> 00:02:07,400
in the country.

42
00:02:07,533 --> 00:02:09,300
Felma would be safe here.

43
00:02:20,433 --> 00:02:21,667
Then, Doctor...

44
00:02:22,900 --> 00:02:27,067
we'll do it here.

45
00:03:02,167 --> 00:03:04,000
So hot.

46
00:03:04,133 --> 00:03:04,967
So...

47
00:03:06,767 --> 00:03:09,733
Felma will have the
operation tomorrow?

48
00:03:09,867 --> 00:03:13,433
Yes.

49
00:03:13,567 --> 00:03:14,433
Perfect.

50
00:03:14,567 --> 00:03:16,967
I should be there.

51
00:03:17,100 --> 00:03:19,967
Do you think Felma will
let you be her caregiver?

52
00:03:21,833 --> 00:03:23,400
Why not?

53
00:03:23,533 --> 00:03:25,100
Remember?

54
00:03:25,233 --> 00:03:27,667
I was upgraded to the
best friend level.

55
00:03:29,700 --> 00:03:31,767
Don't be so confident.

56
00:03:31,900 --> 00:03:32,800
You might end up disappointed.

57
00:03:34,967 --> 00:03:35,800
Oh, please.

58
00:03:37,067 --> 00:03:41,233
Alice, when someone is sick,

59
00:03:41,367 --> 00:03:45,733
they want to be with the person
they feel safe with.

60
00:03:46,600 --> 00:03:47,733
And in Felma's case...

61
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:50,533
it's me, friend.

62
00:03:51,567 --> 00:03:53,233
So I need to be strong.

63
00:03:53,367 --> 00:03:55,900
Because I still have
to take care of a sick person.

64
00:04:09,833 --> 00:04:10,733
Hi.

65
00:04:21,467 --> 00:04:22,433
Hi, friend.

66
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:24,500
How are you feeling?

67
00:04:26,367 --> 00:04:28,900
Are you ready for your
surgery tomorrow?

68
00:04:30,300 --> 00:04:32,533
Because I'm so ready
to take care of you

69
00:04:32,667 --> 00:04:34,433
after your operation.

70
00:04:34,567 --> 00:04:36,867
There's no need.

71
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,533
I don't want you to.

72
00:04:38,667 --> 00:04:40,500
What?

73
00:04:40,633 --> 00:04:42,400
Why?

74
00:04:42,533 --> 00:04:45,533
Because you're someone
who shouldn't be trusted.

75
00:04:45,667 --> 00:04:46,500
Oh, no.

76
00:04:47,500 --> 00:04:48,500
Where did that come from?

77
00:04:50,467 --> 00:04:54,800
From the people I truly trust.

78
00:04:57,033 --> 00:04:58,000
Let me guess.

79
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:02,267
Your family talked ill of me.

80
00:05:03,900 --> 00:05:04,767
Did they?

81
00:05:06,733 --> 00:05:08,433
Your family hates me.

82
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:11,267
What did they say?

83
00:05:13,033 --> 00:05:14,500
They didn't say the details.

84
00:05:16,567 --> 00:05:22,267
The doctor advised them
not to speak with me

85
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:26,167
about bad people or things.

86
00:05:26,300 --> 00:05:28,467
My illness might get worse.

87
00:05:32,333 --> 00:05:33,267
You know what?

88
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:39,833
They think I'm a bad
influence on you.

89
00:05:39,967 --> 00:05:42,000
Yes, sometimes.

90
00:05:42,133 --> 00:05:45,833
I used to ask you to party
with me back then...

91
00:05:45,967 --> 00:05:47,800
to go to bars.

92
00:05:47,933 --> 00:05:49,000
Drink a little.

93
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:52,867
They've made a big deal
out of it.

94
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:58,267
But, friend,
before you reject me,

95
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:01,633
can you answer these questions
first?

96
00:06:01,767 --> 00:06:06,400
Who were with you when you
had a seizure and almost died?

97
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:08,767
Who saved you?

98
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:11,567
Wasn't it me?

99
00:06:12,333 --> 00:06:16,300
When you had a severe headache,

100
00:06:16,433 --> 00:06:19,533
and you had to be brought
to the hospital, right?

101
00:06:19,667 --> 00:06:22,233
Who was with you?

102
00:06:22,367 --> 00:06:23,367
Was it also me?

103
00:06:24,700 --> 00:06:26,967
Where was your family back then?

104
00:06:27,100 --> 00:06:31,700
Didn't they attack me
when they saw me?

105
00:06:31,833 --> 00:06:33,000
You saw it, didn't you?

106
00:06:35,467 --> 00:06:37,300
They really hate me.

107
00:06:39,133 --> 00:06:41,800
But us...

108
00:06:41,967 --> 00:06:43,000
we're good.

109
00:06:44,433 --> 00:06:46,633
Are we really good, Hazel?

110
00:06:49,433 --> 00:06:50,333
Yes, friend.

111
00:06:52,533 --> 00:06:53,633
Very good.

112
00:06:54,867 --> 00:06:55,867
So, please.

113
00:06:57,433 --> 00:06:58,867
Let me take care of you.

114
00:07:06,933 --> 00:07:08,733
Don't tell me...

115
00:07:08,867 --> 00:07:10,533
you're still going to think
about it?

116
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:14,800
I'm going to be upset.

117
00:07:14,967 --> 00:07:17,200
You know I'll take care of you.

118
00:07:17,333 --> 00:07:19,833
I've got you, okay?

119
00:07:19,967 --> 00:07:21,700
Hazel...

120
00:07:21,833 --> 00:07:23,433
What are you doing here?

121
00:07:25,067 --> 00:07:25,933
Manuel...

122
00:07:27,300 --> 00:07:28,867
I'm just visiting Felma.

123
00:07:30,333 --> 00:07:33,800
I'm just wishing her good luck
for her operation tomorrow.

124
00:07:33,933 --> 00:07:35,567
But I'm leaving now.

125
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:38,300
Felma...

126
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:41,033
don't forget my offer.

127
00:07:41,833 --> 00:07:43,600
Let me take care of you.

128
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:46,800
This is for you.

129
00:07:56,233 --> 00:07:57,700
I'll get going.

130
00:07:57,833 --> 00:07:59,333
Bye.

131
00:08:02,300 --> 00:08:04,867
Didn't I tell you to stay away
from Felma?

132
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:08,867
- Manuel
- Leave and never come back! Go!

133
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:10,367
Manuel, wait.

134
00:08:10,500 --> 00:08:12,367
Bye, friend!

135
00:08:12,500 --> 00:08:13,700
Go!

136
00:08:19,133 --> 00:08:20,500
She has left.

137
00:08:28,233 --> 00:08:30,700
So, epic fail?

138
00:08:30,833 --> 00:08:31,867
Well, not yet.

139
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,267
I'm not done yet.

140
00:08:34,500 --> 00:08:36,900
They can't just easily
take me out of the picture.

141
00:08:38,500 --> 00:08:41,700
I won't let my plan fail.

142
00:08:41,833 --> 00:08:44,067
Felma is weak now.

143
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:46,033
She's easy to confuse.

144
00:08:46,167 --> 00:08:48,200
After the operation...

145
00:08:48,333 --> 00:08:52,133
I will try to poison
her mind again.

146
00:08:52,267 --> 00:08:55,267
Convince her that she needs me.

147
00:08:55,433 --> 00:08:58,300
You really won't stop, will you?

148
00:08:58,433 --> 00:09:00,667
When did I ever stop, Alice?

149
00:09:11,467 --> 00:09:14,667
Hazel said...

150
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:18,433
you all hated her...

151
00:09:18,567 --> 00:09:21,367
because she's a bad influence
on me.

152
00:09:22,733 --> 00:09:25,100
But she said...

153
00:09:25,233 --> 00:09:26,767
we're good.

154
00:09:28,300 --> 00:09:31,933
Felma, will you believe her
over your kids?

155
00:09:32,067 --> 00:09:33,500
Over me?

156
00:09:34,933 --> 00:09:36,033
Fine.

157
00:09:36,167 --> 00:09:39,767
After your operation, all your
memories will come back.

158
00:09:39,900 --> 00:09:44,133
You'll realize how evil
and a liar Hazel is.

159
00:09:48,767 --> 00:09:51,433
I might not wake up.

160
00:09:51,567 --> 00:09:53,633
Felma, you will.

161
00:09:55,867 --> 00:09:58,933
What if my memories disappear?

162
00:09:59,067 --> 00:10:01,967
What if I forget our children?

163
00:10:03,167 --> 00:10:05,567
And you?

164
00:10:05,700 --> 00:10:07,767
What if...

165
00:10:07,900 --> 00:10:10,600
What if, I don't recognize you?

166
00:10:10,733 --> 00:10:12,467
Felma.

167
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:14,400
that won't happen.

168
00:10:14,533 --> 00:10:17,533
Felma, listen,
That won't happen.

169
00:10:17,667 --> 00:10:19,733
You're getting the operation

170
00:10:19,867 --> 00:10:23,267
to get rid of what's causing
your memory loss.

171
00:10:26,233 --> 00:10:30,300
But we can't ignore
the possibility...

172
00:10:30,433 --> 00:10:31,533
that something...

173
00:10:32,833 --> 00:10:36,800
that something could go wrong
during the operation.

174
00:10:37,500 --> 00:10:38,867
Okay.

175
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:43,200
Let's say you forget me.

176
00:10:43,333 --> 00:10:45,367
If that happens...

177
00:10:45,500 --> 00:10:50,833
I will not get tired
of introducing myself to you.

178
00:10:50,967 --> 00:10:52,300
Every day...

179
00:10:52,433 --> 00:10:56,667
I'll remind you of what I mean
to your life.

180
00:11:01,800 --> 00:11:05,900
I'm scared.

181
00:11:06,033 --> 00:11:08,633
- Don't be scared.
- I'm scared, Manuel.

182
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:11,433
Don't be scared.

183
00:11:11,567 --> 00:11:14,367
If it doesn't work...

184
00:11:14,500 --> 00:11:16,933
then close your eyes.

185
00:11:17,067 --> 00:11:17,933
Then...

186
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:23,433
listen to your heartbeat.

187
00:11:23,567 --> 00:11:26,567
Feel it.

188
00:11:26,700 --> 00:11:30,100
Your mind might forget me, but..

189
00:11:30,233 --> 00:11:33,067
I'm sure your heart
will remember.

190
00:11:36,433 --> 00:11:37,800
I'm scared.

191
00:11:38,833 --> 00:11:40,567
Felma, don't be scared.

192
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:43,200
What you're afraid of isn't
going to happen.

193
00:11:43,367 --> 00:11:49,867
You'll get out of the OR alive,
safe, and remember all of us.

194
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:50,700
Okay?

195
00:11:50,833 --> 00:11:51,667
Don't be scared.

196
00:11:53,133 --> 00:11:54,967
I'm scared.

197
00:11:57,033 --> 00:11:59,767
I'm scared.

198
00:12:05,300 --> 00:12:07,633
Go to sleep now.

199
00:12:07,767 --> 00:12:10,167
Go to sleep now. That's enough.

200
00:12:22,667 --> 00:12:23,900
Bro.

201
00:12:25,800 --> 00:12:27,433
What's going on?

202
00:12:27,567 --> 00:12:28,400
Bro.

203
00:12:31,333 --> 00:12:33,000
What's happening to you?

204
00:12:33,133 --> 00:12:37,000
You called me here, asked me
to bring beer, and now this?

205
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:42,867
Felma's operation scares me.

206
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:44,367
Come on.

207
00:12:44,500 --> 00:12:47,200
I thought you were the calmest
person I knew.

208
00:12:49,033 --> 00:12:51,567
I'm just pretending to be brave.

209
00:12:51,700 --> 00:12:52,733
In front of you...

210
00:12:53,800 --> 00:12:56,700
and most of all in front
of Felma,

211
00:12:56,833 --> 00:12:57,733
But...

212
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:01,700
Bro.

213
00:13:06,967 --> 00:13:08,567
What if...

214
00:13:08,700 --> 00:13:11,533
something bad happens
to Felma?

215
00:13:11,667 --> 00:13:13,900
What if she doesn't wake up?

216
00:13:15,467 --> 00:13:17,233
Or what if she wakes up...

217
00:13:17,367 --> 00:13:19,400
but forgets all of us?

218
00:13:19,533 --> 00:13:21,767
Why do you think that way?

219
00:13:23,433 --> 00:13:26,333
Felma's going to have
brain surgery.

220
00:13:28,100 --> 00:13:31,133
That's the most delicate part
of our body.

221
00:13:31,267 --> 00:13:33,767
One mistake by the doctor...

222
00:13:33,900 --> 00:13:36,667
could put her in danger.
It could even cost her life.

223
00:13:45,333 --> 00:13:47,800
I won't be able to handle
it if that happens.

224
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:53,400
I won't be able to handle it,
bro.

225
00:13:55,100 --> 00:13:57,933
I still have lots of plans.

226
00:14:00,100 --> 00:14:03,567
And I have a promise to fulfill.

227
00:14:03,700 --> 00:14:06,733
I promised to marry her.

228
00:14:19,733 --> 00:14:20,967
Go on, bro.

229
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:24,200
Just let it all out.

230
00:14:24,333 --> 00:14:26,467
Let it all out.

231
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:30,700
So when you meet Felma again,
you'll be brave in front of her.

232
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:41,067
Felma...

233
00:14:41,200 --> 00:14:42,233
are you ready?

234
00:14:43,933 --> 00:14:45,733
I'm okay now.

235
00:14:45,867 --> 00:14:47,567
Please pray for me, kids.

236
00:14:47,700 --> 00:14:48,800
Yes, Mom.

237
00:14:50,533 --> 00:14:52,900
Mom, we should still see that
smile after your operation.

238
00:14:53,033 --> 00:14:54,400
Okay!

239
00:14:54,533 --> 00:14:56,133
You, too.

240
00:14:56,267 --> 00:14:57,300
Manuel...

241
00:14:57,433 --> 00:14:59,467
if something bad...

242
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:01,700
Nothing bad will happen to you.

243
00:15:06,933 --> 00:15:08,200
Good morning, Miss Felma.

244
00:15:09,467 --> 00:15:11,167
We'll take it from here.

245
00:15:11,300 --> 00:15:14,133
Doctor, please take care of her.

246
00:15:14,267 --> 00:15:15,567
Yes, Mr. Cruz.

247
00:15:18,800 --> 00:15:20,400
Don't be afraid, okay?

248
00:15:23,767 --> 00:15:24,933
Noah...

249
00:15:27,833 --> 00:15:28,767
Jeffrey...

250
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:33,400
Andrea...

251
00:15:35,267 --> 00:15:36,233
Coleen...

252
00:15:37,867 --> 00:15:38,800
Joel...

253
00:15:41,800 --> 00:15:43,033
Manuel...

254
00:15:46,867 --> 00:15:48,833
I can't promise...

255
00:15:52,467 --> 00:15:54,233
but I will try my best...

256
00:15:56,233 --> 00:15:58,433
to remember all of you...

257
00:16:00,067 --> 00:16:01,800
when I come out of here.

258
00:17:46,733 --> 00:17:47,600
Dear.

259
00:17:49,267 --> 00:17:51,300
Felma's operation is today.

260
00:17:53,100 --> 00:17:56,367
I won't pray for it to fail.

261
00:17:58,033 --> 00:17:59,967
Because I'm not that evil.

262
00:18:02,767 --> 00:18:05,333
But if she doesn't survive...

263
00:18:08,667 --> 00:18:10,100
I'll take that...

264
00:18:10,233 --> 00:18:11,967
as a destiny's call.

265
00:18:14,467 --> 00:18:16,967
I'll accept it
with my whole heart.

266
00:18:55,933 --> 00:18:57,367
Dad...

267
00:18:57,500 --> 00:19:00,100
didn't the doctor say
the surgery

268
00:19:00,233 --> 00:19:01,167
would only take four
to six hours?

269
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:04,667
We've been here for almost
eight hours now.

270
00:19:08,300 --> 00:19:12,500
Dear, they said it depends
on how big the tumor is, so...

271
00:19:12,633 --> 00:19:15,467
it might take a little longer.

272
00:19:15,600 --> 00:19:17,400
Be patient, sweetheart.

273
00:19:22,367 --> 00:19:23,200
Friend...

274
00:19:23,333 --> 00:19:25,233
I've been here for hours.

275
00:19:25,367 --> 00:19:28,567
But there's still no news.

276
00:19:28,733 --> 00:19:31,400
Look.

277
00:19:31,533 --> 00:19:32,867
<i> It's okay.</i>

278
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:34,300
I'm willing to wait.

279
00:19:34,433 --> 00:19:37,600
Friend, I haven't slept.
I still have a duty.

280
00:19:37,733 --> 00:19:40,267
Alice, please.
Wait for an update.

281
00:19:40,400 --> 00:19:42,433
<i> Just a little longer, please?</i>

282
00:19:42,567 --> 00:19:44,100
<i> It'll be over soon.</i>

283
00:19:46,667 --> 00:19:47,700
<i> Doctor.</i>

284
00:19:47,833 --> 00:19:48,733
<i> How was it?</i>

285
00:19:48,867 --> 00:19:50,667
<i> How was the operation?</i>

286
00:19:52,433 --> 00:19:53,900
Come on, Doctor.

287
00:19:54,033 --> 00:19:55,000
Come on.

288
00:19:55,133 --> 00:19:56,467
Give me some good news.

289
00:19:56,600 --> 00:19:58,067
<i> We had...</i>

290
00:19:58,200 --> 00:20:00,033
a successful operation.

291
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:03,333
<i> Thank you, Lord!</i>

292
00:20:03,467 --> 00:20:05,200
Felma's safe now!

293
00:20:08,267 --> 00:20:10,567
Thank God.

294
00:20:12,600 --> 00:20:13,700
No!

295
00:20:13,833 --> 00:20:14,900
No!

296
00:20:15,033 --> 00:20:16,500
No, no!

297
00:20:16,633 --> 00:20:18,333
No!

298
00:20:18,467 --> 00:20:20,833
This can't happen? Why?

299
00:20:21,833 --> 00:20:24,067
That can't be!

300
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:29,200
We sent the tumor
for a frozen section, and...

301
00:20:29,333 --> 00:20:31,033
It's benign.

302
00:20:31,167 --> 00:20:32,567
<i> It's non-cancerous.</i>

303
00:20:32,700 --> 00:20:35,000
<i>- Thank God.
- Felma's cancer-free?</i>

304
00:20:38,967 --> 00:20:40,267
<i> Thank God.</i>

305
00:20:42,333 --> 00:20:44,233
<i> Can we see Felma now?</i>

306
00:20:44,367 --> 00:20:46,833
<i>Well, it's going to take
a while...</i>

307
00:20:46,967 --> 00:20:48,133
<i> before she wakes up.</i>

308
00:20:48,267 --> 00:20:50,367
<i>She's still
in the recovery section.</i>

309
00:20:50,500 --> 00:20:53,367
<i>And after that, we'll transfer
her to the ICU.</i>

310
00:20:53,500 --> 00:20:57,100
<i>But Doctor, is everything
all right with Felma?</i>

311
00:20:57,233 --> 00:20:59,733
<i>Everything went well
throughout the surgery.</i>

312
00:20:59,867 --> 00:21:02,833
<i>And we'll know more
when she wakes up.</i>

313
00:21:02,967 --> 00:21:06,767
<i> But everything is good.</i>

314
00:21:06,900 --> 00:21:08,200
<i> She made it through the worst.</i>

315
00:21:09,700 --> 00:21:12,467
<i>- Thank you,
- Thank you Doctor, thank you.</i>

316
00:21:12,600 --> 00:21:14,367
<i> Alice...</i>

317
00:21:14,500 --> 00:21:16,667
it feels like I'm watching
a movie...

318
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:20,067
with an ending I hate.

319
00:21:25,133 --> 00:21:27,433
Make sure you give this
to the doctors, nurses,

320
00:21:27,567 --> 00:21:29,767
and staff who handled
your mom's surgery.

321
00:21:29,900 --> 00:21:31,067
And then go home after.

322
00:21:31,200 --> 00:21:33,300
So you can take a rest.

323
00:21:33,433 --> 00:21:36,200
Dad, you just want Mom
all to yourself, okay?

324
00:21:37,700 --> 00:21:39,100
Please no, Dad.

325
00:21:39,233 --> 00:21:42,700
We want us to be here
when Mom wakes up.

326
00:21:42,867 --> 00:21:45,933
We don't know what time
she'll wake up.

327
00:21:46,067 --> 00:21:48,367
And you still have to
go to work tomorrow.

328
00:21:48,500 --> 00:21:49,667
Yeah, Jeff and Andeng.

329
00:21:49,800 --> 00:21:52,233
We still have a meeting at FMP.

330
00:21:52,367 --> 00:21:55,100
And you, you still
have school tomorrow.

331
00:21:55,233 --> 00:21:58,033
And I have something
to attend to in Davao.

332
00:21:58,167 --> 00:22:00,433
I'll go ahead.

333
00:22:00,567 --> 00:22:02,467
Noah, is that urgent?

334
00:22:02,600 --> 00:22:04,833
Can you wait until
Felma wakes up?

335
00:22:42,200 --> 00:22:43,233
Felma...

336
00:22:47,067 --> 00:22:49,967
Love, I told you nothing
bad would happen.

337
00:22:52,100 --> 00:22:53,500
Please wake up soon.

338
00:22:55,933 --> 00:22:57,633
So you can regain your strength.

339
00:23:08,267 --> 00:23:09,467
Felma?

340
00:23:11,433 --> 00:23:12,400
Love.

341
00:23:23,767 --> 00:23:25,400
Noah.
